When a compiler can’t compile my code, the thing I’m always most curious to know is “what is the first thing it found that was wrong?” And the compiler will usually tell you that in the first error message it prints out – at the top of the bunch of lines it prints out. If you fix the first error, many times all the rest of the errors disappear when you try to compile your program again, because the first error was throwing the compiler off.

In your case, the first error line I can see is probably not the first error you got when you compiled. But it may be close to the first error, because it is saying that something was required by the statement on line 33 of SwerveModule.h, around column 64 (the error iine before that, which you didn’t post here yet, probably said what the thing was that was required). I notice that the wpilib SwerveBot Example code SwerveModule.h file doesn’t have anything on line 33 (it’s a blank line) so maybe some change that you made near there, or above there, is what is causing your problem.

If you don’t figure it out, post the first error lines your compiler prints here, and some of the C/C++ experts will take a look.
